description.narrative: (India): .This Public Private Partnership (PPP) stewardship activity focuses on strengthening the capacity of the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (MOHFW) to use technology and private sector partnerships/solutions to improve access to quality healthcare, including MCH and FP...FY 2018 funds will be used to: 1) support MOHFW to establish systems for voluntary engagement of private health care providers to provide antenatal care services to high-risk pregnant women; 2) automate MOHFW's annual budget of $7 billion through an integrated software solution and establish digital monitoring systems to track financial and programmatic progress of health programs including MCH and FP; 3) assist the MOHFW to implement a pan-India scale-up of India's first patient feedback system across public hospitals, and use the feedback to improve quality of MCH and FP programs; 4) support innovative private sector models for child and maternal healthcare services in Assam and Madhya Pradesh. .. .
